Document: StatusIndicator
Path: godot/classes/class_statusindicator.rst
Summary: Properties and methods for configuring a StatusIndicator's icon, menu, tooltip, and visibility in Godot.

Property: icon (Texture2D): Status indicator icon. Method: set_icon(value: Texture2D). Method: get_icon() → Texture2D.

Property: menu (NodePath): Status indicator native popup menu. Default: NodePath(""). Method: set_menu(value: NodePath). Method: get_menu() → NodePath. Note: Native popup is only supported if NativeMenu supports FEATURE_POPUP_MENU feature. If set, the pressed signal is not emitted.

Property: tooltip (String): Status indicator tooltip. Default: "". Method: set_tooltip(value: String). Method: get_tooltip() → String.

Property: visible (bool): If true, the status indicator is visible. Default: true. Method: set_visible(value: bool). Method: is_visible() → bool.
---CHUNK---
Document: StatusIndicator
Path: godot/classes/class_statusindicator.rst
Summary: Returns the status indicator's screen-space rectangle and visibility state

Method: get_rect() → Rect2 (const)
Returns the status indicator rectangle in screen coordinates. If this status indicator is not visible, returns an empty Rect2.